channel.title: Tough Songs for Audiosurf
channel.description:
Hope I posted this in the right place... [/SIZE]
I was playing Audiosurf this afternoon (mostly lame songs like Sophie Ellis-Bextor's Murder On The Dancefloor and *cough* Britney Spears *cough*[/SIZE]), when I realized I don't have that many... [i]red songs[/i], or songs with a high in-game traffic congestion. I guess I'm a coward, and besides my lappie lags a lot when I play :frowning: So I was wondering if you guys know any particular song that's interesting to play there :wink:
The hardest songs I've played so far are Scooter's [url='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3tj6DDdzAQc']The Logical Song[/url], with a traffic congestion of 307, and Turmion Kätilöt's [url='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8gPyLXw7f-Y']U.S.C.H![/url], with a nice traffic congestion of 314. Maybe they don't sound so difficult to play, but they surely gave me a headache.
Any other suggestions for fellow Audiosurf players to rage at? :stuck_out_tongue:

item.title: Tough Songs for Audiosurf
item.dc:creator: Door
item.description:
Some of the Cowboy Bebop music can be quite fast, but I’ve only played them on Ninja Mono Ironmode so I don’t know what they’re like on the easier characters.

Yeah Yeah Yeahs - Zero. Takes a while to get started but the middle to end is great fun
Another one in the same album is Heads Will Roll, fast-ish throughout.

I’m surprised Hamst3r didn’t recommend any of the Hamster Alliance’s music, some of it’s nice and fast. I don’t remember specific track names though.

Rammstein - Pussy is a good one for medium-ish speed.

Songs by Binaerpilot are generally fast too.

Contact me if ya need help gettin’ them :3

item.title: Tough Songs for Audiosurf
item.dc:creator: Hamst3r
item.description:
Audiosurf tricks: Enabling Iron Mode makes Audiosurf quite a bit crazier. There are more blocks on the track, your ship moves faster and there are more rolls and more hazards and penalties.

In addition to that, add [as-steep] to the ID3 tag of the mp3 to make Audiosurf react more to the music.

That’s the best way to play. [as-steep] Iron Mode. Add [as-swind] if you’re a real masochist - it enables Sidewinder mode where the track moves horizontally rather than vertically.
